The paper also deals with fairness, which is a topic of growing interest in the field of artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The paper also involves optimization and decision-making, which are key components of robotics, making cs.RO (Robotics) a possible category. The paper also involves game theory, which is a subfield of computer science that deals with decision-making in strategic situations, making cs.GT (Game Theory) a possible category. Finally, the paper involves ethical considerations, which could fall under the category of cs.CY (Computers and Society).
